                            <comment id="16288250" author="elyograg" created="Tue, 12 Dec 2017 20:47:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that uses deprecated HttpClient stuff.  Also re-introduces a couple of boolean-related methods that perhaps should be done another way.  The patch would probably work, but I don&apos;t think it&apos;s a very good one.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16288293" author="elyograg" created="Tue, 12 Dec 2017 21:25:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With some help from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hossman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hossman&quot;&gt;hossman&lt;/a&gt;, I was able to eliminate the deprecated code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Apparently directly setting things like the hostname verifier can be overridden by other configuration, particularly by setting an SSL context.  I didn&apos;t see that being done in the code, but it&apos;s something that could be added later.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I did put nocommit in the patch &amp;#8211; I think we need a test that can verify that disabling hostname verification with a sysprop actually works.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
